boxId.name: boxId
boxId.description: The type of chassis used in the concentrator. For modular concentrators, the hardware is further qualifed by the value of cardId for each card installed in the concentrator.

boxDescr.name: boxDescr
boxDescr.description: A textual description of the chassis including the ODS model number, media type and number of slots. For modular concentrators, the hardware is further qualified by the value of cardDescr for each card installed in the concentrator.

boxNetworkMode.name: boxNetworkMode
boxNetworkMode.description: The state of the network interface port. If the value is network(2), the concentrator may be cas- caded off of another network. Regardless of the value, the concentrator may also be connected to other networks via normal interface ports. Note that the functionality previously provided by this object has been superceded by portOperStatus and portAdminStatus as all external connections on the concentrator are available through the portTable. This object may be deleted from future versions of the MIB.

boxPowerStatus.name: boxPowerStatus
boxPowerStatus.description: The state of the power supplies in the concentrator. The value is a sum. For each power supply P, in the range 1 through 2, that is operational, 2 raised to (P - 1) is added to the sum. For example, if both power supplies are good, the value is 3 (2^0 + 2^1). In contrast, if power supply 2 is bad, the value is 1 (2^0). Note that the value will be NULL for those concentrators which can not access the power supply status.

boxNumAddresses.name: boxNumAddresses
boxNumAddresses.description: The number of unique, physical, source and dest- ination addresses contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminAddrStat- Enable is disabled(2).

boxGoodPackets.name: boxGoodPackets
boxGoodPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxGoodOctets.name: boxGoodOctets
boxGoodOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxCrcErrors.name: boxCrcErrors
boxCrcErrors.description: The number of packets received by the concen- trator which had CRC errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStat- Enable is disabled(2).

boxAlignErrors.name: boxAlignErrors
boxAlignErrors.description: The number of packets received by the concen- trator which had frame alignment errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxFragErrors.name: boxFragErrors
boxFragErrors.description: The number of packets received by the concen- trator which contained fewer than 64 octets. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxPacketThresh.name: boxPacketThresh
boxPacketThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of non- errored packets received by the concentrator. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a box-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of non-errored packets per second received by the concentrator.

boxOctetThresh.name: boxOctetThresh
boxOctetThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator. If the measured number of octets per second equals or exceeds this value, a box- class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of octets per second contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator.

boxCrcThresh.name: boxCrcThresh
boxCrcThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received by the concentrator which had CRC errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a box-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received by the concentrator which had CRC errors.

boxAlignThresh.name: boxAlignThresh
boxAlignThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received by the concentrator which had frame alignment errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a box-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitor- ing of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received by the concentrator which had frame alignment errors.

boxFragThresh.name: boxFragThresh
boxFragThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received by the concentrator which contained fewer than 64 octets. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a box-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitor- ing of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received by the concentrator which contained fewer than 64 octets.

boxMissedPackets.name: boxMissedPackets
boxMissedPackets.description: The number of packets received by the concen- trator which could not be processed by the agent due to excessive network traffic.

boxLostPackets.name: boxLostPackets
boxLostPackets.description: The number of packets received by the concen- trator which could not be attributed to a card and port by the agent. This object is not main- tained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpUnkPackets.name: bpUnkPackets
bpUnkPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an unknown protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpIPPackets.name: bpIPPackets
bpIPPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a DOD (IP, ARP, RARP) protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpISOPackets.name: bpISOPackets
bpISOPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an ISO protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpDECPackets.name: bpDECPackets
bpDECPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a DEC protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpNWPackets.name: bpNWPackets
bpNWPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a NetWare protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpATPackets.name: bpATPackets
bpATPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an AppleTalk protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpXNSPackets.name: bpXNSPackets
bpXNSPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an XNS protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpSNAPackets.name: bpSNAPackets
bpSNAPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an SNA protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpUnkOctets.name: bpUnkOctets
bpUnkOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an unknown protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpIPOctets.name: bpIPOctets
bpIPOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a DOD (IP, ARP, RARP) protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of admin- ProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpISOOctets.name: bpISOOctets
bpISOOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an ISO protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpDECOctets.name: bpDECOctets
bpDECOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a DEC protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpNWOctets.name: bpNWOctets
bpNWOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having a NetWare protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpATOctets.name: bpATOctets
bpATOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an AppleTalk protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpXNSOctets.name: bpXNSOctets
bpXNSOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an XNS protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

bpSNAOctets.name: bpSNAOctets
bpSNAOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having an SNA protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxAddressTable.name: boxAddressTable
boxAddressTable.description: A list of address entries for each physical address contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator. The number of entries is given by the value of boxNumAddresses. Note that no entries are maintained if the value of admin- AddrStatEnable is disabled(2).

boxAddressEntry.name: boxAddressEntry
boxAddressEntry.description: An address entry containing objects pertaining to a physical address contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator.

batCard.name: batCard
batCard.description: The card on which the most recent, non-errored packet having the address as source was received. The card identified by this value is the same card as identified by the same value of cardIndex. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not transmitted packets.

batPort.name: batPort
batPort.description: The port on which the most recent, non-errored packet having the address as source was received. The port identified by this value is the same port as identified by the same value of portIndex. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not transmitted packets.

batPhysAddress.name: batPhysAddress
batPhysAddress.description: The physical address for this entry. When reported in a trap, the physical address relevant to the trap.

batLastIpAddress.name: batLastIpAddress
batLastIpAddress.description: The source network address used in the most recent IP packet received by the concentrator having the address as source. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not transmitted any IP packets or if the value of adminIpCheckEnable is disabled(2).

batGoodPackets.name: batGoodPackets
batGoodPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source.

batGoodOctets.name: batGoodOctets
batGoodOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source.

batFirstPacket.name: batFirstPacket
batFirstPacket.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the first packet having the address as source was received by the concentrator. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not transmitted packets.

batLastPacket.name: batLastPacket
batLastPacket.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the most recent packet having the address as source was received by the concentrator. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not transmitted packets.

batGoodPacketsTo.name: batGoodPacketsTo
batGoodPacketsTo.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as dest- ination.

batGoodOctetsTo.name: batGoodOctetsTo
batGoodOctetsTo.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as destination.

batFirstPacketTo.name: batFirstPacketTo
batFirstPacketTo.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the first packet having the address as destination was received by the concentrator. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not been sent packets.

batLastPacketTo.name: batLastPacketTo
batLastPacketTo.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the most recent packet having the address as destination was received by the concentrator. Note that the value will be NULL for addresses which have not been sent packets.

batDelete.name: batDelete
batDelete.description: Setting this object to any legal, ASN.1 value deletes the entry for the address.

addrProtoTable.name: addrProtoTable
addrProtoTable.description: A list of protocol entries for each physical address contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator. The number of entries is given by the value of boxNumAddresses. Note that no entries are maintained if the value of admin- AddrStatEnable is disabled(2).

addrProtoEntry.name: addrProtoEntry
addrProtoEntry.description: A protocol entry containing objects pertaining to a physical address contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator.

apPhysAddress.name: apPhysAddress
apPhysAddress.description: The physical address for this entry.

apUnkPackets.name: apUnkPackets
apUnkPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an unknown protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStat- Enable is disabled(2).

apIPPackets.name: apIPPackets
apIPPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a DOD (IP, ARP, RARP) protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apISOPackets.name: apISOPackets
apISOPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an ISO protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apDECPackets.name: apDECPackets
apDECPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a DEC protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apNWPackets.name: apNWPackets
apNWPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a NetWare protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apATPackets.name: apATPackets
apATPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an AppleTalk protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStat- Enable is disabled(2).

apXNSPackets.name: apXNSPackets
apXNSPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an XNS protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apSNAPackets.name: apSNAPackets
apSNAPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an SNA protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apUnkOctets.name: apUnkOctets
apUnkOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an unknown protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apIPOctets.name: apIPOctets
apIPOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a DOD (IP, ARP, RARP) protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apISOOctets.name: apISOOctets
apISOOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an ISO protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apDECOctets.name: apDECOctets
apDECOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a DEC protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apNWOctets.name: apNWOctets
apNWOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and a NetWare protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apATOctets.name: apATOctets
apATOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an AppleTalk protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apXNSOctets.name: apXNSOctets
apXNSOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an XNS protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

apSNAOctets.name: apSNAOctets
apSNAOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received by the concentrator having the address as source and an SNA protocol type. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminProtStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardNumSlots.name: cardNumSlots
cardNumSlots.description: The number of slots in the concentrator. For modular concentrators, this value is the maximum number of cards that can be installed. For non-modular concentrators, the value is always two (card one contains the user ports and card two contains the network port).

cardNumCards.name: cardNumCards
cardNumCards.description: The number of cards actually installed in the concentrator. For non-modular concentrators, the value is always two (card one contains the user ports and card two contains the network port).

cardTable.name: cardTable
cardTable.description: A list of card entries for each card installed in the concentrator. The number of entries is given by the value of cardNumCards.

cardEntry.name: cardEntry
cardEntry.description: A card entry containing objects pertaining to a card installed in the concentrator.

cardIndex.name: cardIndex
cardIndex.description: The slot in which the card is installed. This value uniquely identifies the card. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of cardNumSlots. When reported in a trap, the card relevant to the trap.

cardId.name: cardId
cardId.description: The type of card installed in the concentrator. For non-modular concentrators, the value is the same as that of boxId.

cardDescr.name: cardDescr
cardDescr.description: A textual description of the card including the ODS model number, media type and number of ports. For non-modular concentrators, the value is the same as that of boxDescr.

cardOperStatus.name: cardOperStatus
cardOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the card. Note that this object currently has no meaning and may be deleted from future versions of the MIB.

cardAdminStatus.name: cardAdminStatus
cardAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the card. Note that this object currently has no meaning and may be deleted from future versions of the MIB.

cardNetworkMode.name: cardNetworkMode
cardNetworkMode.description: The state of the back-plane connection on the card. If the value is stand-alone(3), the ports on the card form a separate, isolated network from the rest of the cards in the concentrator. If the value is unsupported(1), the card is always connected and can not be changed.

cardNumPorts.name: cardNumPorts
cardNumPorts.description: The number of configurable ports on the card. For some cards, the value may be zero.

cardNumAddresses.name: cardNumAddresses
cardNumAddresses.description: The number of unique, physical, source addresses contained in non-errored packets received on the card. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminAddrStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardGoodPackets.name: cardGoodPackets
cardGoodPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received on the card. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardGoodOctets.name: cardGoodOctets
cardGoodOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received on the card. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardCrcErrors.name: cardCrcErrors
cardCrcErrors.description: The number of packets received on the card which had CRC errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardAlignErrors.name: cardAlignErrors
cardAlignErrors.description: The number of packets received on the card which had frame alignment errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardFragErrors.name: cardFragErrors
cardFragErrors.description: The number of packets received on the card which contained fewer than 64 octets. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of admin- PktStatEnable is disabled(2).

cardPacketThresh.name: cardPacketThresh
cardPacketThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of non- errored packets received on the card. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a card-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of non-errored packets per second received on the card.

cardOctetThresh.name: cardOctetThresh
cardOctetThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of octets contained in non-errored packets received on the card. If the measured number of octets per second equals or exceeds this value, a card-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of octets per second contained in non-errored second received on the card.

cardCrcThresh.name: cardCrcThresh
cardCrcThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the card which had CRC errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a card-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received on the card which had CRC errors.

cardAlignThresh.name: cardAlignThresh
cardAlignThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the card which had frame alignment errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a card-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received on the card which had frame alignment errors.

cardFragThresh.name: cardFragThresh
cardFragThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the card which contained fewer than 64 octets. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a card-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received on the card which contained fewer than 64 octets.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: A list of port entries for each interface port in the concentrator. The number of entries is given by the sum of cardNumPorts for each card in the cardTable.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: A port entry containing objects pertaining to an interface port in the concentrator.

portCard.name: portCard
portCard.description: The card on which the port exists. The card identified by this value is the same card as identified by the same value of cardIndex. When reported in a trap, the card relevant to the trap.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: An integer which uniquely identifes this port on the card. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of cardNumPorts for the card. When reported in a trap, the port relevant to the trap.

portOperStatus.name: portOperStatus
portOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the port. If the value is down(2), no data is passed through the port.

portAdminStatus.name: portAdminStatus
portAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the port. If the value is down(2), no data is passed through the port. When reported in a trap, the new state of the port. If the value is down(2), the port was turned off as a result of the auto-shutoff feature being enabled.

portLinkStatus.name: portLinkStatus
portLinkStatus.description: The link status for the port. For media types that do not support link status, the value is always unsupported(1). When reported in a trap, the new link status of the port.

portAutoOffEnable.name: portAutoOffEnable
portAutoOffEnable.description: The state of the auto-shutoff feature for the port. If the value is enabled(1), the value of portAdminStatus for the port will be changed to down(1) whenever a port threshold is exceeded.

portAddrTrapEnable.name: portAddrTrapEnable
portAddrTrapEnable.description: The state of the new-address detection feature for the port. If the value is enabled(1), a newAddressTrap will be generated whenever a new, physical, source address is contained in a packet received by the concentrator on the port.

portNumAddresses.name: portNumAddresses
portNumAddresses.description: The number of unique, physical, source addresses contained in non-errored packets received on the port. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminAddrStatEnable is disabled(2).

portGoodPackets.name: portGoodPackets
portGoodPackets.description: The number of non-errored packets received on the port. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

portGoodOctets.name: portGoodOctets
portGoodOctets.description: The number of octets contained in non-errored packets received on the port. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

portCrcErrors.name: portCrcErrors
portCrcErrors.description: The number of packets received on the port which had CRC errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

portAlignErrors.name: portAlignErrors
portAlignErrors.description: The number of packets received on the port which had frame alignment errors. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2).

portFragErrors.name: portFragErrors
portFragErrors.description: The number of packets received on the port which contained fewer than 64 octets. Note that this object is not maintained if the value of admin- PktStatEnable is disabled(2).

portPacketThresh.name: portPacketThresh
portPacketThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of non- errored packets received on the port. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a port-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of non-errored packets per second received on the port.

portOctetThresh.name: portOctetThresh
portOctetThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of octets contained in non-errored packets received on the port. If the measured number of octets per second equals or exceeds this value, a port-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of octets per second contained in non-errored second received on the port.

portCrcThresh.name: portCrcThresh
portCrcThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the port which had CRC errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a port-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per secondreceived on the port which had CRC errors.

portAlignThresh.name: portAlignThresh
portAlignThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the port which had frame alignment errors. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a port-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received on the port which had frame alignment errors.

portFragThresh.name: portFragThresh
portFragThresh.description: A threshold for monitoring the number of packets received on the port which contained fewer than 64 octets. If the measured number of packets per second equals or exceeds this value, a port-class trap will be sent to each network manager defined in the adminTrapTable. Monitoring of this threshold is disabled if the value is zero or if the value of adminPktStatEnable is disabled(2). When reported in a trap, the measured number of packets per second received on the port which contained fewer than 64 octets.

adminReboot.name: adminReboot
adminReboot.description: Setting this object to any legal, ASN.1 value recycles the management agent in the concentrator.

adminLocalTime.name: adminLocalTime
adminLocalTime.description: The local time of day at the concentrator. The value is a string of three binary-coded-decimal octets in the form HH MM SS, where HH is the hour (24 hour format), MM is the minutes and SS is the seconds. The local time of day is only used for out-of- band management via the asynchronous port on the concentrator.

adminLocalDate.name: adminLocalDate
adminLocalDate.description: The local date at the concentrator. The value is a string of three binary-coded-decimal octets in the form YY MM DD, where YY is the year, MM is the month and DD is the day. The local date is only used for out-of-band management via the asynchronous port on the concentrator.

adminSecureTerm.name: adminSecureTerm
adminSecureTerm.description: The status of the out-of-band interface. If the value is secured(1), the user is be required to enter a super-user level community name before any management functions can be accessed.

adminPrivilege.name: adminPrivilege
adminPrivilege.description: The access privilege afforded the community name used in the requesting PDU. This value allows a network manager to easily determine its ability to read and write protected objects.

adminTrapId.name: adminTrapId
adminTrapId.description: The number of unique traps generated by the agent since it was reset. When reported in a trap, an integer which uniquely identifies the trap.

adminTrapAddress.name: adminTrapAddress
adminTrapAddress.description: When reported in a trap, the source IP address of a PDU which resulted in an authentication failure.

adminPktStatEnable.name: adminPktStatEnable
adminPktStatEnable.description: The state of the packet statistics collection feature. If the value is enabled(1), the management agent will maintain statistics for all packets received by the concentrator on a box, card and port basis. The value is normally enabled(1). It should only be set to disabled(2) during periods of excessively high network traffic when the management agent must remain available for other management activities.

adminAddrStatEnable.name: adminAddrStatEnable
adminAddrStatEnable.description: The state of the address statistics collection feature. If the value is enabled(1), the manage- ment agent will maintain statistics for all packets received by the concentrator on a physical, source and destination address basis. The value is normally enabled(1) but can be set to disabled(2) when address-related statistics are not needed. It should be set to disabled(2) during periods of excessively high network traffic when the management agent must remain available for other management activities.

adminProtStatEnable.name: adminProtStatEnable
adminProtStatEnable.description: The state of the protocol statistics collection feature. If the value is enabled(1), the manage- ment agent will maintain statistics for all packets received by the concentrator on a top-level protocol basis. The value is normally disabled(2). It should only be set to enabled(1) when protocol-related statis- tics are needed as it adversely affects performance of the management agent in the concetrator.

adminIpCheckEnable.name: adminIpCheckEnable
adminIpCheckEnable.description: The state of the IP address detection feature. If the value is enabled(1) and the value of adminAddr- StatEnable is also enabled(1), the management agent will detect the IP address used by each physical source address in any TCP/IP packets received by the concentrator. The value is normally disabled(2). It should only be set to enabled(1) when protocol-related statis- tics are needed as it adversely affects performance of the management agent in the concetrator.

accMaxEntries.name: accMaxEntries
accMaxEntries.description: The maximum number of access privilege entries allowed in adminAccessTable.

adminAccessTable.name: adminAccessTable
adminAccessTable.description: A list of access entries mapping community names into access privileges. The maximum number of entries is given by accMaxEntries.

adminAccessEntry.name: adminAccessEntry
adminAccessEntry.description: An access entry which maps a community name into an access privilege.

accIndex.name: accIndex
accIndex.description: An integer which uniquely identifies this entry.

accCommunity.name: accCommunity
accCommunity.description: The community name for the entry. Setting this object to a null string effectively invalidates the entry. However, accDelete should be used to delete entries as it resets all parameters to default settings.

accPrivilege.name: accPrivilege
accPrivilege.description: The access privilege afforded the community name in the entry.

accDelete.name: accDelete
accDelete.description: Setting this object to any legal, ASN.1 value deletes the entry for the community name.

trapMaxEntries.name: trapMaxEntries
trapMaxEntries.description: The maximum number of network manager entries allowed in adminTrapTable.

adminTrapTable.name: adminTrapTable
adminTrapTable.description: A list of trap entries for each network manager which receives traps from the agent. The maximum number of entries is given by trapMaxEntries.

adminTrapEntry.name: adminTrapEntry
adminTrapEntry.description: A trap entry containing objects pertaining to a network manager which receives traps from the agent.

trapDestAddress.name: trapDestAddress
trapDestAddress.description: The IP address of the management station to receive traps. Note that setting this object to a value of all zeros effectively invalidates the entry. However, trapDelete should be used to delete entries as it resets all parameters to default settings.

trapCommunity.name: trapCommunity
trapCommunity.description: The community name used in traps sent to the management station.

trapStdEnable.name: trapStdEnable
trapStdEnable.description: The state of the standard-class trap enable for the management station. If the value is disabled(2), standard SNMP traps will not be sent.

trapBoxEnable.name: trapBoxEnable
trapBoxEnable.description: The state of the box-class trap enable for the management station. If the value is disabled(2), box-class traps will not be sent.

trapCardEnable.name: trapCardEnable
trapCardEnable.description: The state of the card-class trap enable for the management station. If the value is disabled(2), card-class traps will not be sent.

trapPortEnable.name: trapPortEnable
trapPortEnable.description: The state of the port-class trap enable for the management station. If the value is disabled(2), port-class traps will not be sent.

trapAddrEnable.name: trapAddrEnable
trapAddrEnable.description: The state of the address-class trap enable for the management station. If the value is disabled(2), address- class traps will not be sent.

trapDelete.name: trapDelete
trapDelete.description: Setting this object to any legal, ASN.1 value deletes the entry for the management station.
